hi Gordon,

it only seems to happen pretty occasionally, on moderately large crawls 
(3000 seed URLs, max-docs set to 100 per seed (in the RobegerFrontier).

here&#39;s an example excerpt from recover.gz:


% gunzip &lt; recover.gz | fgrep http://216.219.253.36
Fe http://216.219.253.36/
F+ http://216.219.253.36/robots.txt P http://216.219.253.36/
F+ http://216.219.253.36/
Fe http://216.219.253.36/robots.txt
Fs http://216.219.253.36/robots.txt
Fe http://216.219.253.36/
Fs http://216.219.253.36/
...

None of the seed URLs I input contained IP addresses (they were all domain 
names), so it seems maybe suspicious that this problem popped up with an IP 
address.  I&#39;m wondering if somehow the IP address was emitted from an 
earlier discvoery of a DNS-name-containing URL, and somehow it got 
translated into an IP address-containing URL in the recover log.

thanks,
  - Mike

